WEBVTT

00:01.436 --> 00:03.046
<i>Previously</i> <i>
on "Resident Alien"...</i>

00:03.090 --> 00:04.482
Open up. It's me.

00:04.526 --> 00:05.744
When we went to that
charity thing in New York,

00:05.788 --> 00:07.355
they said that the money
was for the clinic.

00:07.398 --> 00:08.486
Okay, you need to calm down.

00:08.530 --> 00:10.053
Calm down? I can't calm down.

00:10.097 --> 00:11.272
They're threatening
our families.

00:11.315 --> 00:13.013
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:13.056 --> 00:14.144
- Um...
- Sorry.

00:14.188 --> 00:17.626
- It's okay. I gotta go.
- Right. Got it.

00:17.669 --> 00:19.628
[device beeping]
- It's receiving a signal.

00:19.671 --> 00:21.325
What does it say?

00:21.369 --> 00:23.327
It's a phone number.

00:23.371 --> 00:25.329
Pack your bags.
We're going to New York.

00:25.373 --> 00:26.852
<i>Too many people.</i>

00:26.896 --> 00:28.680
<i>The last island that had</i> <i>
this many humans on it</i>

00:28.724 --> 00:31.509
<i>was Atlantis, and that did not</i> <i>
turn out well.</i>

00:31.553 --> 00:34.164
Hey, I would like
two slices of pepperoni.

00:34.208 --> 00:35.426
Anything else?

00:35.470 --> 00:37.080
Does an alien live here?

00:37.124 --> 00:39.082
This is the number you got.

00:39.126 --> 00:41.693
Something has to be here.

00:41.737 --> 00:44.914
It says "Goliath."

00:44.957 --> 00:47.264
I am marking every one

00:47.308 --> 00:48.744
of Goliath's murals
in the city.

00:48.787 --> 00:51.138
That is where
we will find Goliath.

00:51.181 --> 00:52.878
What can I get you?

00:52.922 --> 00:54.184
What do you got?

00:54.228 --> 00:56.882
Someone here must be Goliath.

00:56.926 --> 00:59.059
Does anyone look
alien to you?

00:59.102 --> 01:01.974
Everything you need to know
about Goliath is on the canvas.

01:02.018 --> 01:05.630
Goliath believes acid helps
you shed your human chains.

01:05.674 --> 01:08.633
<i>I would like to shed</i> <i>
my human chains.</i>

01:08.677 --> 01:09.634
[growls]

01:09.678 --> 01:10.766
[shrieks]

01:11.941 --> 01:13.551
[yelps]

01:13.595 --> 01:15.684
How long have you known
Harry's an alien?

01:15.727 --> 01:17.773
<i>♪</i>

01:17.816 --> 01:20.776
This is some bullshit.

01:22.343 --> 01:25.172
<i>[upbeat music playing</i> <i>
over radio]</i>

01:25.215 --> 01:26.521
<i>♪</i>

01:26.564 --> 01:29.306
[humming]

01:29.350 --> 01:32.701
<i>♪</i>

01:32.744 --> 01:35.704
[horse chuffing]

01:35.747 --> 01:42.667
<i>♪</i>

01:44.452 --> 01:48.020
[horse nickers]
[speaking Portuguese]

01:48.064 --> 01:49.326
[horse chuffs]
[hooves clopping]

01:49.370 --> 01:52.460
[speaking Portuguese]

01:53.983 --> 01:57.421
[shouting in Portuguese]

01:57.856 --> 01:59.510
[speaking Portuguese]

02:02.383 --> 02:05.386
<i>[ominous music]</i>

02:05.429 --> 02:07.953
[speaking Portuguese]

02:07.997 --> 02:14.873
<i>♪</i>

02:33.240 --> 02:35.111
[gasps]

02:35.155 --> 02:42.118
<i>♪</i>

02:42.162 --> 02:44.033
[creature growls]

02:44.076 --> 02:45.774
[speaking Portuguese]

02:47.036 --> 02:48.168
[grunts]

02:51.388 --> 02:58.526
<i>♪</i>

03:04.096 --> 03:07.056
<i>[Brown Bird's "Bilgewater"]</i>

03:07.099 --> 03:10.015
<i>[laid-back acoustic strumming]</i>

03:10.059 --> 03:14.368
<i>♪</i>

03:14.411 --> 03:17.501
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

03:17.545 --> 03:19.155
<i>When I first came to Earth,</i>

03:19.199 --> 03:21.549
<i>I thought I would be watching</i> <i>
the death--</i>

03:21.592 --> 03:24.465
<i>The colors are exploding</i> <i>
everywhere!</i>

03:24.508 --> 03:26.031
[horn blares] <i>
Ooh!</i>

03:26.075 --> 03:27.511
<i>Watching the death</i>

03:27.555 --> 03:29.339
<i>of all these humans</i> <i>
from my ship</i>

03:29.383 --> 03:31.298
<i>after I dropped my device.</i>

03:31.341 --> 03:33.561
<i>Things have changed.</i>

03:33.604 --> 03:35.040
[hisses]

03:35.084 --> 03:36.346
<i>♪</i>

03:36.390 --> 03:39.915
What makes you think
Harry's an alien?

03:39.958 --> 03:41.221
Come with me.

03:41.264 --> 03:44.311
[indistinct chatter]

03:44.354 --> 03:46.313
<i>[R&B music playing</i> <i>
over speakers]</i>

03:46.356 --> 03:47.879
[panel beeping]

03:56.018 --> 03:58.716
You're nervous. I understand.
But don't be.

03:58.760 --> 04:01.458
I know who Harry is,
and I know why you're here.

04:01.502 --> 04:04.244
How?
How do you know that?

04:04.287 --> 04:06.594
I recognize his energy.

04:07.638 --> 04:10.815
Goliath grew to love it here,
but it was never natural.

04:10.859 --> 04:14.079
He lived with a lot
of inner turmoil.

04:14.123 --> 04:15.951
You can see it in his art.

04:15.994 --> 04:17.909
Wait, you said "lived"?

04:17.953 --> 04:20.825
What--please tell me
that Goliath is here.

04:20.869 --> 04:22.262
Goliath is here.

04:22.305 --> 04:23.480
[inhales deeply]

04:23.524 --> 04:25.482
Okay.
[exhales heavily]

04:30.661 --> 04:31.967
[gasps]

04:32.010 --> 04:33.534
What is this?

04:34.491 --> 04:35.971
This is Goliath.

04:36.014 --> 04:38.582
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

04:38.626 --> 04:42.760
I don't understand.

04:42.804 --> 04:44.414
After Goliath came to Earth,

04:44.458 --> 04:46.895
we became
each other's whole world.

04:46.938 --> 04:48.200
But his great wish

04:48.244 --> 04:50.986
was to connect
with one of his people again.

04:51.029 --> 04:54.903
The signal that brought you
here was a personal invitation.

04:54.946 --> 04:56.339
<i>♪</i>

04:56.383 --> 04:59.603
Goliath held out
for as long as he could.

04:59.647 --> 05:02.432
But six months ago, he--

05:02.476 --> 05:05.392
well, you can see for yourself.

05:06.654 --> 05:08.960
Their species fossilize
when they die.

05:09.004 --> 05:11.180
No, this can't be.

05:11.223 --> 05:13.051
Goliath cannot be dead.

05:13.095 --> 05:14.401
We came all this way,

05:14.444 --> 05:16.316
and you don't understand
what's at stake!

05:16.359 --> 05:18.100
I'm sorry.
This is all there is.

05:18.143 --> 05:19.449
[exhales heavily]

05:19.493 --> 05:21.321
If you came here to speak
with Goliath,

05:21.364 --> 05:22.539
that's not going to happen.

05:22.583 --> 05:25.673
[phone ringing]

05:26.935 --> 05:28.806
Oh, God.

05:28.850 --> 05:30.721
<i>♪</i>

05:30.765 --> 05:33.855
Oh, my God.
What happened?

05:33.898 --> 05:35.422
You are alien.

05:35.465 --> 05:39.643
<i>Well, I took some LSD</i> <i>
on my tongue.</i>

05:39.687 --> 05:45.736
And now I'm surrounded
by horrible creatures.

05:45.780 --> 05:46.650
[gasps]

05:46.694 --> 05:49.436
I just saw an alien

05:49.479 --> 05:52.090
take off its head,

05:52.134 --> 05:54.136
and there was a human inside!

05:54.919 --> 05:56.921
<i>Do I have a human</i> <i>
inside of me?</i>

05:58.270 --> 06:00.664
How many licks does it take

06:00.708 --> 06:03.275
to get to the human?

06:03.319 --> 06:05.626
[whimpers]

06:05.669 --> 06:06.975
New York City Public Library.

06:07.018 --> 06:08.585
Okay, I know where you are.
Don't go anywhere.

06:08.629 --> 06:10.108
<i>I will be right there.</i>

06:10.152 --> 06:13.111
<i>♪</i>

06:13.155 --> 06:14.374
[whimpers]

06:14.417 --> 06:21.555
<i>♪</i>

06:23.818 --> 06:24.775
[screams]

06:29.476 --> 06:30.912
Feeling better?

06:31.478 --> 06:32.740
Yes.

06:34.655 --> 06:37.397
The ice is stabilizing
my human form.

06:41.226 --> 06:45.230
I saw so many humans today.

06:45.274 --> 06:47.624
Humans are gross.

06:47.668 --> 06:51.628
But...they have each other.

06:53.369 --> 06:56.546
Like those two--
- Harry.

06:59.941 --> 07:00.898
[sighs]

07:04.380 --> 07:05.947
This is their home.

07:07.470 --> 07:10.168
I want to meet someone like me

07:10.212 --> 07:13.345
so maybe...

07:13.389 --> 07:15.522
I can feel like I am home.

07:15.565 --> 07:17.437
<i>♪</i>

07:17.480 --> 07:20.701
Yeah, about that.

07:20.744 --> 07:23.573
I spoke to Violinda
at the party.

07:23.617 --> 07:25.488
She knows Goliath.

07:27.098 --> 07:29.405
Or did know him.

07:29.449 --> 07:33.453
<i>♪</i>

07:33.496 --> 07:35.280
He's dead, Harry.

07:35.324 --> 07:40.285
<i>♪</i>

07:40.329 --> 07:44.638
Goliath was dead as soon as
he became more human than me.

07:44.681 --> 07:51.688
<i>♪</i>

07:51.732 --> 07:54.648
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

07:54.691 --> 07:59.130
<i>♪</i>

07:59.174 --> 08:00.523
Hmm.

08:00.567 --> 08:07.574
<i>♪</i>

08:32.207 --> 08:34.905
<i>[soft music]</i>

08:34.949 --> 08:40.911
<i>♪</i>

08:40.955 --> 08:42.391
[soft clattering]

08:44.175 --> 08:45.307
[door clicks open]

08:45.350 --> 08:46.569
- Hey.
- Hi.

08:46.613 --> 08:47.875
- You're home early.
- Yeah.

08:47.918 --> 08:49.529
Ah.
How are you?

08:49.572 --> 08:50.660
How was your mom?

08:50.704 --> 08:53.228
Well, turns out,
by "quality time,"

08:53.271 --> 08:55.099
she meant 24-7 tech support.

08:55.143 --> 08:56.536
- Mm.
- So...

08:56.579 --> 08:58.146
What have you been up to?
- Nothin'.

08:58.189 --> 08:59.364
Yeah, doin' nothin'.

08:59.408 --> 09:00.714
Just alone.
Alone vibes.

09:00.757 --> 09:01.715
You know, vibin' it.

09:01.758 --> 09:03.238
- Nice.
- Mm-hmm.

09:03.281 --> 09:05.022
Okay.
Let me take this upstairs.

09:05.066 --> 09:06.328
Nope!
Ah, wouldn't hear of it.

09:06.371 --> 09:07.721
I'll take this up later.

09:07.764 --> 09:09.070
Okay. Thank you.

09:09.113 --> 09:10.158
Mm-hmm.

09:10.201 --> 09:12.726
<i>[quirky music]</i>

09:12.769 --> 09:15.903
Oh, would you grab Max's bag?
He went to Sahar's.

09:15.946 --> 09:17.165
Yeah.

09:17.208 --> 09:24.346
<i>♪</i>

09:34.878 --> 09:36.227
[sighs]

09:37.838 --> 09:38.752
Huh.

09:44.192 --> 09:46.150
That's weird.

09:46.194 --> 09:47.848
Yeah, weird.
How did--how did that happen?

09:47.891 --> 09:49.545
- Hmm.
- Hmm.

09:49.589 --> 09:51.547
Oh, wow.

09:51.591 --> 09:52.592
You put that up.

09:53.897 --> 09:54.985
Wasn't it in the closet?

09:55.029 --> 09:56.770
- You hate it.
- No, I don't.

09:56.813 --> 09:58.815
A lot of people
have that in their homes.

09:58.859 --> 10:00.295
Okay, I'll take it down.

10:00.338 --> 10:01.992
No. If you wanna keep it up,
you should keep it up.

10:02.036 --> 10:03.907
- Do you want me to keep it up?
- I want what you want.

10:03.951 --> 10:06.388
I want what you want.
You know, if you want.

10:09.565 --> 10:11.045
Did you move
the coffee table?

10:11.088 --> 10:12.263
Yeah, I'll just take it down.

10:21.708 --> 10:23.057
Morning.

10:23.100 --> 10:25.450
Hey, Liv.

10:25.494 --> 10:28.323
Oh, I was thinking
of starting a donation jar

10:28.366 --> 10:29.846
for the coffeepots.

10:29.890 --> 10:31.761
You know, you shouldn't
have to pay for those yourself.

10:31.805 --> 10:33.415
Thank you.

10:33.458 --> 10:35.809
I really appreciate that.

10:35.852 --> 10:40.074
Why--why are you putting
that sign in here?

10:40.117 --> 10:42.293
Well, I thought
you might like it.

10:42.337 --> 10:44.208
You know, bring just
a real artistic statement

10:44.252 --> 10:45.601
into the office.

10:45.645 --> 10:47.951
What do you--
what do you think?

10:48.735 --> 10:52.390
Do I have to say I like it
for you to do the donation jar?

10:53.696 --> 10:56.046
I...

10:56.090 --> 10:57.091
love it.

10:57.134 --> 10:58.570
Great!
It stays up.

10:58.614 --> 11:00.311
I'll--I'll get a jar.
- Okay.

11:00.355 --> 11:02.270
Hey, can I show you something
real quick?

11:02.313 --> 11:03.880
Yeah, you bet.

11:03.924 --> 11:05.969
I think I'm going
to post this video.

11:06.013 --> 11:08.058
"Incredible UFO in Patience."

11:08.102 --> 11:09.538
No, you can't post that.

11:09.581 --> 11:11.758
You know, people already
think Patience

11:11.801 --> 11:13.107
is a murder town.

11:13.150 --> 11:15.065
You want them to think
it's an alien town too?

11:15.109 --> 11:16.545
But if this is real,

11:16.588 --> 11:19.679
don't I owe it to the world
to share this?

11:19.722 --> 11:21.376
Yeah, as long as you
change the headline

11:21.419 --> 11:24.466
to "Incredible UFO
Near Jessup."

11:24.509 --> 11:25.685
Backspace.
- Hey.

11:25.728 --> 11:27.121
Oh.

11:27.164 --> 11:28.949
Jab me in the arm.

11:28.992 --> 11:30.124
Seems like a lawsuit.

11:30.167 --> 11:31.299
Oh, is it?

11:31.342 --> 11:33.736
Oh, look at this.

11:33.780 --> 11:35.564
Am I jabbing myself?
I can't feel anything.

11:35.607 --> 11:36.957
You know why?
'Cause I cut myself

11:37.000 --> 11:38.698
this morning on the fence
and needed stitches,

11:38.741 --> 11:41.526
and Dr. Smallwood put
my whole damn arm to sleep.

11:41.570 --> 11:44.051
How am I supposed to work with
a dead tree-trunk arm, huh?

11:44.094 --> 11:45.139
Oh, let me see.
Let's see how.

11:45.182 --> 11:46.401
Let me just grab a pen.

11:48.272 --> 11:49.578
Oh, look at that.

11:49.621 --> 11:50.884
Deputy, looks like
you gonna have to write

11:50.927 --> 11:52.015
my police reports today.

11:52.059 --> 11:53.887
I already do that, sir.

11:53.930 --> 11:55.149
Well, good.

11:55.192 --> 11:56.324
Then we're prepared.

11:59.370 --> 12:00.894
Look, I'm sure
that it's a simple mistake.

12:00.937 --> 12:03.679
I mean, Dr. Smallwood
is an institution.

12:03.723 --> 12:05.768
She literally delivered me
as a baby.

12:05.812 --> 12:08.379
Didn't she literally
deliver your parents too?

12:08.423 --> 12:09.467
Yeah,
I don't think that's relevant.

12:09.511 --> 12:10.860
Look, you need
to fire her ass

12:10.904 --> 12:12.079
before a bunch of elves

12:12.122 --> 12:13.428
move into
my tree-trunk arm here

12:13.471 --> 12:14.777
and start making cookies.

12:14.821 --> 12:17.040
One mistake should not ruin
a woman's life.

12:17.084 --> 12:18.302
It's more than one mistake!

12:18.346 --> 12:19.826
I saw her for a sore throat,

12:19.869 --> 12:22.045
and she diagnosed me
with hysteria.

12:22.916 --> 12:27.224
I think that you're both
blowing this out of proportion.

12:27.268 --> 12:28.835
You know,
I'm getting the results today

12:28.878 --> 12:30.140
for my yearly checkup,

12:30.184 --> 12:32.055
and I am sure that she
will be as spry as ever.

12:32.099 --> 12:34.144
You know, last time I saw her,
she did a cartwheel.

12:34.188 --> 12:37.800
No, she didn't.

12:37.844 --> 12:38.845
But I bet she could.

12:40.977 --> 12:42.370
Seen enough?

12:42.413 --> 12:43.980
I really don't
wanna miss the flight.

12:44.024 --> 12:47.636
I wanted to see this one
Goliath mural before we left.

12:48.985 --> 12:55.035
I did not think
I would miss my octopus friend,

12:55.078 --> 12:58.908
because I thought
I was meeting alien family.

12:58.952 --> 13:01.563
But now they're both dead.

13:01.606 --> 13:04.827
I feel very alone.

13:04.871 --> 13:07.047
I'm sorry you didn't get
to see family on this trip.

13:07.090 --> 13:08.744
No Goliath...

13:08.788 --> 13:12.269
no idea how we're gonna
save the world.

13:12.313 --> 13:15.359
What are we gonna do now?
- I do not know.

13:15.403 --> 13:17.187
Goliath was our last chance

13:17.231 --> 13:19.668
to contact my planet

13:19.711 --> 13:23.498
and my last chance to meet
one of my people on Earth.

13:23.541 --> 13:26.066
Now I will die
without having a conversation

13:26.109 --> 13:27.589
in my beautiful language.

13:27.632 --> 13:30.418
I will be forced
to talk to myself.

13:30.461 --> 13:33.464
[speaking alien language]

13:36.816 --> 13:38.600
I'd tell you to keep it down,
but we're in New York.

13:38.643 --> 13:40.254
Weird is normal here, so...

13:40.297 --> 13:43.344
[speaking alien language]

13:45.955 --> 13:51.047
Do you think Goliath
had an octopus friend too?

13:51.091 --> 13:52.396
Maybe.

13:52.440 --> 13:53.876
I don't know
how his mind worked, though.

13:53.920 --> 13:55.878
Maybe this painting
is just random.

13:55.922 --> 13:57.488
It is not random.

13:57.532 --> 14:00.622
Everything my people do
has purpose.

14:00.665 --> 14:02.102
Okay, well,
it's really confusing,

14:02.145 --> 14:04.800
'cause it feels like he
brought us here for no reason.

14:04.844 --> 14:07.934
Not confusing. Impossible.

14:07.977 --> 14:09.500
<i>Goliath knew of me,</i>

14:09.544 --> 14:11.459
<i>knew that I was stranded.</i>

14:11.502 --> 14:12.982
<i>However human he had become,</i>

14:13.026 --> 14:15.550
<i>he would never have brought me</i> <i>
here without a reason.</i>

14:16.943 --> 14:19.902
Are you sure Goliath did not
leave anything for me?

14:19.946 --> 14:22.818
Violinda
didn't mention anything.

14:22.862 --> 14:25.125
Do you think
she is hiding something?

14:25.168 --> 14:26.953
I don't know.

14:26.996 --> 14:29.825
I mean, she seemed like
she was genuinely grieving.

14:29.869 --> 14:33.394
She was really sad
when she showed me his body.

14:33.437 --> 14:36.440
You saw Goliath's dead body?

14:36.484 --> 14:37.702
Yeah.

14:37.746 --> 14:39.139
You could've told me
that your people

14:39.182 --> 14:40.488
turned to stone when they died

14:40.531 --> 14:42.707
or that they die standing up,
for that matter.

14:42.751 --> 14:44.666
He was standing up?

14:44.709 --> 14:46.624
Goliath was standing?

14:46.668 --> 14:48.496
Yes, his dead body was.

14:48.539 --> 14:50.324
- [yelping excitedly]
- What?

14:50.367 --> 14:53.109
I have--we have to go.

14:53.153 --> 14:55.329
Harry!

14:55.372 --> 14:58.506
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

15:02.945 --> 15:05.687
<i>[L7's "Pretend We're Dead"]</i>

15:05.730 --> 15:07.776
<i>♪ Come on, come on,</i> <i>
come on, come on ♪</i>

15:07.819 --> 15:09.778
<i>♪</i>

15:09.821 --> 15:11.911
<i>♪ Come on, come on,</i> <i>
come on, come on ♪</i>

15:11.954 --> 15:13.825
<i>♪</i>

15:13.869 --> 15:16.002
<i>♪ Come on, come on,</i> <i>
come on, come on ♪</i>

15:16.045 --> 15:18.221
<i>♪</i>

15:18.265 --> 15:19.570
<i>♪ Come on, come on,</i> <i>
come on, come on ♪</i>

15:19.614 --> 15:21.964
<i>♪ When we pretend</i> <i>
that we're dead ♪</i>

