come on, come on ♪</i>

15:48.730 --> 15:51.080
<i>♪ Dead</i>

15:51.124 --> 15:53.169
<i>♪ Pretend we're dead</i>

15:53.213 --> 15:55.780
<i>♪ Dead</i>

15:55.824 --> 15:58.870
<i>♪ Come on, come on,</i> <i>
come on, come on ♪</i>

15:58.914 --> 16:00.176
<i>♪ We're dead</i>

16:00.220 --> 16:02.657
[breathing heavily]

16:02.700 --> 16:04.964
She murdered her husband,

16:05.007 --> 16:07.705
and now she's profiting
from his stuff.

16:07.749 --> 16:09.969
This here is a murder sale.

16:10.012 --> 16:11.144
That's what you
called us out here for?

16:11.187 --> 16:12.362
- Uh-huh.
- Look.

16:12.406 --> 16:14.103
Mrs. Hodges
is currently awaiting trial

16:14.147 --> 16:16.018
on the crime
that she is accused of.

16:16.062 --> 16:18.368
She has every legal right
to have a yard sale,

16:18.412 --> 16:20.109
which is more than I can say
about you and that shirt.

16:20.153 --> 16:21.719
Now, why don't you
take your ass home

16:21.763 --> 16:24.244
before a flock of flamingos
come lookin' for they daddy?

16:31.947 --> 16:33.296
Thank you, Sheriff.

16:33.340 --> 16:36.169
I'm just an impartial
administrator of the law.

16:36.212 --> 16:38.780
Well, I'm probably gonna box
all this up anyway.

16:38.823 --> 16:42.392
Apparently, nobody wants to buy
antique spoons from a murderer,

16:42.436 --> 16:44.916
so I'll probably just
take it all to Goodwill.

16:44.960 --> 16:46.179
Hold on a minute.

16:46.222 --> 16:48.007
Look at this. Hey, Deputy.

16:48.050 --> 16:49.182
Look at this.

16:49.225 --> 16:51.053
Who do I look like?

16:51.097 --> 16:52.750
A hipster poet?

16:52.794 --> 16:55.231
No. Dick Tracy, damn it.

16:55.275 --> 16:56.972
Greatest detective in history.

16:57.016 --> 16:58.974
Invented the watch phone.

16:59.018 --> 17:01.107
Never saw a dime
of the profits, though.

17:01.150 --> 17:03.109
Because he was
a cartoon character?

17:03.152 --> 17:04.327
How much you want for this?

17:05.850 --> 17:08.201
I don't know.
20 bucks?

17:08.244 --> 17:10.507
- Sold.
- It's a good deal.

17:10.551 --> 17:12.422
It was Sam's.
He only wore it once.

17:13.380 --> 17:14.642
We were flying to Montana,

17:14.685 --> 17:16.252
and he left his old hat
on the plane,

17:16.296 --> 17:18.689
so he got that one
at the airport.

17:18.733 --> 17:20.082
<i>[somber music]</i>

17:20.126 --> 17:21.779
He looked really cute in it.

17:21.823 --> 17:24.086
<i>♪</i>

17:24.130 --> 17:25.218
Listen, Sheriff, I'm sorry.

17:25.261 --> 17:28.090
I've changed my mind.
I can't sell it.

17:28.134 --> 17:29.961
<i>♪</i>

17:30.005 --> 17:31.659
Okay.
It's no problem.

17:31.702 --> 17:34.053
<i>♪</i>

17:34.096 --> 17:35.967
[clears throat]

17:36.011 --> 17:38.796
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

17:38.840 --> 17:41.756
<i>♪</i>

17:41.799 --> 17:44.193
Let's see what else
we got around here.

17:44.237 --> 17:46.848
[chuckles]
I remember these.

17:46.891 --> 17:48.458
Sam loved
these mystery novels.

17:48.502 --> 17:50.112
Always trying
to get me to read one.

17:50.156 --> 17:51.722
Told me it would help me
solve crimes.

17:51.766 --> 17:52.941
[chuckles]

17:52.984 --> 17:55.291
All right, tell you what.
I'll give you...

17:55.335 --> 17:56.684
50 bucks
for the whole lot of them.

17:56.727 --> 17:59.687
Oh, no, no.
Sheriff, that's too much.

17:59.730 --> 18:01.732
Listen,
if Sam wanted you to have them,

18:01.776 --> 18:03.604
then you don't pay.

18:03.647 --> 18:07.086
Just consider it a gift
from Sam to you.

18:08.217 --> 18:10.089
Thank you, Mrs. Hodges.
That's very kind.

18:10.132 --> 18:12.178
<i>[somber music]</i>

18:12.221 --> 18:13.744
Yeah, all right.

18:13.788 --> 18:15.703
Deputy?
- Mm. Mm-hmm.

18:15.746 --> 18:18.836
<i>♪</i>

18:18.880 --> 18:21.230
She seem like a woman
who killed her husband to you?

18:22.753 --> 18:24.103
No, sir, she doesn't.

18:24.146 --> 18:27.149
No, that's grief right there.
Plain and simple.

18:27.193 --> 18:28.585
I mean, a woman
who kills her husband

18:28.629 --> 18:31.110
don't hang on to no old hat
just to remember him by.

18:31.153 --> 18:37.507
<i>♪</i>

18:50.390 --> 18:51.913
<i>And Bloom goes down.</i>

18:51.956 --> 18:54.263
D'arcy,
you had a bad fall.

18:54.307 --> 18:55.873
<i>They said I could've</i> <i>
lost my leg</i>

18:55.917 --> 18:57.048
<i>or even died.</i>

18:57.092 --> 19:00.051
<i>[ominous music]</i>

19:00.095 --> 19:01.662
<i>♪</i>

19:04.360 --> 19:07.276
<i>[quirky music]</i>

19:07.320 --> 19:14.283
<i>♪</i>

19:14.327 --> 19:16.546
[buttons beeping]

19:16.590 --> 19:21.551
<i>♪</i>

19:21.595 --> 19:23.727
Oh, you're going that way?
- [laughs]

19:23.771 --> 19:24.902
That's weird.

19:24.946 --> 19:26.121
Hey.

19:26.165 --> 19:28.079
I didn't know
you worked out here.

19:28.123 --> 19:30.647
Yeah, I--
I took a recovery day.

19:32.780 --> 19:33.781
For about 15 years.

19:33.824 --> 19:35.913
[laughs]
Glad to have you back.

19:35.957 --> 19:37.828
[buttons beeping]

19:41.049 --> 19:42.920
Oh, you're at a six?

19:42.964 --> 19:45.140
That's cute. I'm at a seven.

19:45.184 --> 19:47.011
You need glasses.

19:47.055 --> 19:49.057
That's an eight.

19:49.100 --> 19:50.885
[buttons beeping]

19:52.321 --> 19:54.454
Sure you can handle that?

19:54.497 --> 19:56.325
Aren't you
a little out of practice?

19:56.369 --> 19:57.979
I have an advantage.

19:58.022 --> 20:00.329
Stopped being able to feel
my legs after I did squats.

20:01.548 --> 20:04.638
<i>[Blues Saraceno's "Evil Ways"]</i>

20:04.681 --> 20:11.122
<i>♪</i>

20:11.166 --> 20:13.342
<i>♪ Oh</i>

20:13.386 --> 20:14.517
<i>♪ Hey</i>

20:14.561 --> 20:15.910
<i>♪ My evil ways</i>
- One more.

20:15.953 --> 20:16.911
You got it.

20:16.954 --> 20:19.479
[grunts]

20:19.522 --> 20:21.394
That is gonna hurt tomorrow.

20:21.437 --> 20:22.873
Yeah, but it's a good hurt.

20:22.917 --> 20:25.485
My coach always says
it's gotta hurt to work.

20:25.528 --> 20:27.574
- College?
- Yeah.

20:27.617 --> 20:30.316
I ran the 1,500
and 5,000 at CU.

20:30.359 --> 20:32.970
Got second in the NCAA finals
my senior year.

20:33.014 --> 20:35.059
Legit.

20:35.103 --> 20:36.800
Hoo.

20:36.844 --> 20:38.193
Oh, you okay?

20:38.237 --> 20:40.282
Yeah, yeah.
Think I overdid it.

20:40.326 --> 20:42.632
Just need some water.
- Yeah, I get it.

20:42.676 --> 20:44.765
I almost blew chunks
all over poor Mr. Gibbons

20:44.808 --> 20:46.897
on the elliptical.

20:46.941 --> 20:48.029
All right, I'm done.

20:48.072 --> 20:49.073
Let's head over to The 59.

20:49.117 --> 20:50.901
Got some protein shakes.

20:50.945 --> 20:52.686
- You do?
- Yeah.

20:52.729 --> 20:53.817
Well, beers.

20:53.861 --> 20:55.515
It's got half a gram
of protein in it.

20:55.558 --> 20:56.994
I mean, it's better than that
garbage you're drinking anyway.

20:57.038 --> 20:58.082
What is that?

20:58.126 --> 21:00.041
- It's water.
- Ugh.

21:00.084 --> 21:00.998
[whispering] Water.

21:01.042 --> 21:03.436
[banging on door]

21:05.046 --> 21:06.787
I need to see Goliath.

21:06.830 --> 21:08.005
Please stop.

21:08.049 --> 21:09.311
I told you he passed on.

21:09.355 --> 21:10.834
I wish you would
respect my privacy.

21:10.878 --> 21:12.488
I tried.
But I can't stop him.

21:12.532 --> 21:14.185
Where is Goliath?

21:14.229 --> 21:15.491
You need to leave.

21:15.535 --> 21:17.319
Harry, we have to leave.

21:17.363 --> 21:18.755
She wants us to go.

21:18.799 --> 21:19.756
Asta.

21:25.371 --> 21:26.502
This way.

21:26.546 --> 21:29.200
No.
No, you can't be here!

21:29.244 --> 21:32.334
<i>[tense music]</i>

21:32.378 --> 21:33.335
[gasps]

21:33.379 --> 21:35.729
<i>♪</i>

21:35.772 --> 21:37.208
[gasps]

21:37.252 --> 21:42.779
<i>♪</i>

21:42.823 --> 21:45.042
No!
No!

21:45.086 --> 21:47.044
[grunts]

21:47.088 --> 21:53.877
<i>♪</i>

21:58.926 --> 22:00.928
What the hell is that?

22:00.971 --> 22:01.885
[candlestick clatters]

22:01.929 --> 22:02.973
[sighs]

22:03.017 --> 22:04.366
It's our baby.

22:04.410 --> 22:09.763
<i>♪</i>

22:14.071 --> 22:15.638
You need to leave.

22:15.682 --> 22:17.205
I'm not letting you
take my child.

22:17.248 --> 22:20.817
I could just rip
your arms off.

22:20.861 --> 22:22.906
Stop it. What do you mean,
that's your baby?

22:22.950 --> 22:25.822
Goliath used my genetic
tissue to get pregnant.

22:25.866 --> 22:29.130
Goliath contacted me.
This is why.

22:29.173 --> 22:31.959
Hello?
Anyone here?

22:32.742 --> 22:33.874
I'll take care of it.

22:35.615 --> 22:37.399
Sorry, the door was open.

22:37.443 --> 22:39.401
Are you Violinda Darvell?

22:39.445 --> 22:40.707
Yes.

22:40.750 --> 22:42.404
We're not open quite yet.

22:42.448 --> 22:43.492
You'll have to leave.

22:43.536 --> 22:44.667
I'm a little desperate.

22:44.711 --> 22:45.973
I'm interested
in buying some art,

22:46.016 --> 22:47.627
and I was told
you might be able to help.

22:47.670 --> 22:49.237
An artist named Goliath?

22:49.280 --> 22:52.109
Unfortunately,
I'm busy right now.

22:52.153 --> 22:53.807
Are you sure
you can't spare a few minutes?

22:53.850 --> 22:55.896
<i>You're a freakin' Picasso!</i>

22:55.939 --> 22:58.028
Did you draw this picture?

22:58.072 --> 23:00.596
Yeah, I draw police
composites of criminals.

23:00.640 --> 23:03.425
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

23:03.469 --> 23:05.209
Oh, shit.

23:07.951 --> 23:09.910
Here you go.
On the house.

23:09.953 --> 23:12.216
Oh, thank you.
That's very generous.

23:12.260 --> 23:14.262
[chuckles]

23:14.305 --> 23:15.437
Mm.

23:16.699 --> 23:18.571
This tastes like soap.

23:18.614 --> 23:20.094
Oh, yeah. Sorry.

23:20.137 --> 23:22.531
It's a local brewery,

23:22.575 --> 23:24.359
which means it's just a guy
that makes beer in his bathtub.

23:24.403 --> 23:25.491
I'll get you
a different kind--

23:25.534 --> 23:27.493
No, no.
That's not it.

23:28.624 --> 23:30.278
Oh, no.

23:30.321 --> 23:31.366
What?

23:31.410 --> 23:33.455
The last time
that this happened,

23:33.499 --> 23:36.327
I was in my first trimester
with Max.

23:37.503 --> 23:39.853
Plus the dizziness
at the gym...

23:40.810 --> 23:42.464
You think you're pregnant?

23:42.508 --> 23:43.857
I think so.

23:44.684 --> 23:46.120
I mean, congratulations.

23:46.163 --> 23:47.295
We gotta get some champagne.

23:47.338 --> 23:49.515
I can't drink
if I'm pregnant.

23:50.777 --> 23:53.475
I know.

23:53.519 --> 23:56.478
[sighs]

23:56.522 --> 23:58.785
What's wrong?

23:58.828 --> 24:03.354
I just don't know how I feel
about having another kid.

24:03.398 --> 24:04.791
Oh, right.

24:04.834 --> 24:07.228
'Cause of Max.
- What do you mean?

24:07.271 --> 24:09.448
I didn't--what do you mean?
What do you mean?

24:09.491 --> 24:12.886
Having another kid
means my entire life

24:12.929 --> 24:15.671
gets put on hold
for the next 18 years.

24:15.715 --> 24:17.238
I have to reset the clock.

24:18.892 --> 24:20.894
Of course,
Ben would be thrilled.

24:20.937 --> 24:22.112
[laughs]

24:23.723 --> 24:26.029
I mean, he would.

24:27.074 --> 24:29.380
Are you sure he would?

24:29.424 --> 24:31.948
Why?
Did he say something to you?

24:31.992 --> 24:33.515
Why would he say anything
to me?

24:33.559 --> 24:35.212
It's not like we sit around
having conversations

24:35.256 --> 24:36.649
about you guys having kids,
right?

24:36.692 --> 24:38.738
Yeah.

24:38.781 --> 24:39.913
Maybe he changed his mind.

24:39.956 --> 24:41.871
You know,
I change my mind all the time.

24:41.915 --> 24:44.526
Like, earlier, I was sure
I was gonna have only one beer,

24:44.570 --> 24:46.615
and now I'm thinking
I might have six.

24:46.659 --> 24:48.138
Trust me.

24:48.182 --> 24:49.705
I know my husband.

24:49.749 --> 24:51.751
He wants more kids.

24:51.794 --> 24:53.056
He'd start a family band
if he could.

24:53.100 --> 24:54.449
Yeah, that's--he's--

24:54.493 --> 24:56.364
you know,
you know your husband.

25:00.281 --> 25:04.067
Ah, right on time, as always. Punctual.

25:04.111 --> 25:05.982
You're a great doctor.
- Thank you.

25:06.026 --> 25:09.072
Unfortunately,
I have some bad news for you.

25:09.116 --> 25:10.552
What's that?

25:10.596 --> 25:13.990
Your blood tests indicate
cancer in your colon.

25:14.034 --> 25:16.558
It's very aggressive.

25:16.602 --> 25:18.908
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

25:18.952 --> 25:19.996
Ah.

25:20.040 --> 25:21.998
That's Mrs. Patel's chart.

25:22.042 --> 25:25.393
- Whoops.
- This is Ben Hawthorne's.

25:26.394 --> 25:28.222
Wait.

25:28.265 --> 25:31.007
So I don't have cancer?

25:31.051 --> 25:32.574
No.

25:32.618 --> 25:34.576
Low in vitamin D.

25:35.751 --> 25:37.057
Get some sun.

25:37.100 --> 25:39.233
Have a good day.

25:39.276 --> 25:41.365
Don't tell Mrs. Patel
if you see her.

25:41.409 --> 25:42.715
Yikes.

25:42.758 --> 25:44.586
Sorry, hang on.

25:44.630 --> 25:47.850
Dr. Smallwood, you basically
just told me that I was dying.

25:47.894 --> 25:49.722
I had the wrong chart.

25:49.765 --> 25:50.723
It happens.
- Should it?

25:50.766 --> 25:51.941
No.

25:51.985 --> 25:52.942
Could you
give us some privacy?

25:52.986 --> 25:54.074
Also no.

25:54.117 --> 25:56.642
[sighs]
Okay, well...

25:56.685 --> 26:00.515
Dr. Smallwood,
I am sorry to have to do this.

26:00.559 --> 26:03.692
I mean, you will always be
a pillar of this community.

26:03.736 --> 26:05.433
But I am going to have to...

26:08.436 --> 26:10.699
Ask you
if you have ever considered

26:10.743 --> 26:12.092
taking an extended vacation.

26:12.135 --> 26:14.094
You know, maybe buy a van?
See the world?

26:14.137 --> 26:15.574
- He's trying to fire you.
- Mm.

26:15.617 --> 26:17.184
You're not the doctor
you used to be,

26:17.227 --> 26:18.664
and if you keep working here,

26:18.707 --> 26:20.143
you might kill someone.

26:21.231 --> 26:22.624
Is this true?

26:24.147 --> 26:26.323
It's not not true.

26:26.367 --> 26:29.805
You're a sweet boy for not
wanting to tell me that.

26:29.849 --> 26:32.025
You're not sweet at all.

26:32.068 --> 26:34.549
It even looked like
you enjoyed it.

26:34.593 --> 26:37.334
I didn't not enjoy it.

26:38.771 --> 26:40.468
[sighs]

26:40.511 --> 26:42.992
And now
we officially have no doctor.

26:49.520 --> 26:51.522
I pulled out our hiring files
when I realized

26:51.566 --> 26:54.308
Smallwood was about to tell you
you were dying.

26:54.351 --> 26:56.527
Seems like you had time
to stop her, but okay.

26:56.571 --> 26:58.965
Dr. Vanderspeigle
is our only real candidate.

26:59.008 --> 27:01.402
Good doctor
but not much to look at.

27:01.445 --> 27:03.143
He's a Patience six,
which is a Denver four,

27:03.186 --> 27:04.797
which is a California one.

27:04.840 --> 27:07.060
Not sure if any of that's
legal to say.

27:09.018 --> 27:10.672
He has a birthday coming up.

27:10.716 --> 27:12.282
You know,
maybe I could convince him.

27:12.326 --> 27:13.936
Sneaky.
Buy him a present.

27:13.980 --> 27:15.503
Soften him up.

27:15.546 --> 27:18.680
You've just moved up
to a Patience three.

27:19.986 --> 27:21.248
Thanks.

27:22.379 --> 27:24.686
Goliath pieces
are very rare.

27:24.730 --> 27:28.124
You could try the curator
at the Guggenheim.

27:28.168 --> 27:29.648
I certainly can't help you.

27:29.691 --> 27:31.432
[whispering]
I could just kill her.

27:31.475 --> 27:32.476
[whispering]
No. No more killing.

27:32.520 --> 27:33.739
Just a minute.
She'll leave.

27:35.131 --> 27:36.306
Hmm.

27:37.873 --> 27:39.005
What about this piece?

27:39.048 --> 27:40.484
This is a Goliath.

27:40.528 --> 27:42.356
It's part
of my personal collection.

27:42.399 --> 27:44.488
It's not for sale.
- Hmm.

27:45.751 --> 27:47.535
Seems like it means
a lot to you.

27:49.755 --> 27:51.408
Did you know him?

27:51.452 --> 27:53.933
I don't think
that's any of your business.

27:53.976 --> 27:55.369
You need to leave now.

27:56.805 --> 27:57.806
Don't take this the wrong way,

27:57.850 --> 27:59.112
but I can tell
by looking at you,

27:59.155 --> 28:00.983
you can't afford
a piece like this.

28:01.027 --> 28:03.246
[chuckles]

28:03.290 --> 28:05.379
You'd be surprised
by my resources.

28:05.422 --> 28:08.164
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

28:08.208 --> 28:09.644
<i>♪</i>

28:09.688 --> 28:10.732
What's in the bag?

28:12.125 --> 28:14.562
[suppressed gunshot]
- [shouts]

28:14.605 --> 28:21.221
<i>♪</i>

28:25.747 --> 28:27.227
[grunts]

28:27.270 --> 28:28.750
[suppressed gunshots]
- No!

28:28.794 --> 28:29.882
[suppressed gunshots,
glass shattering]

28:29.925 --> 28:31.492
<i>♪</i>

28:31.535 --> 28:32.580
[suppressed gunshot]
- [shouts]

28:34.974 --> 28:36.453
[grunts]

28:36.497 --> 28:38.194
[panting]

28:38.238 --> 28:40.588
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

28:40.631 --> 28:42.416
I'm sorry.
You're right.

28:42.459 --> 28:44.505
Goliath wanted you
to have the egg.

28:44.548 --> 28:46.899
It's why you were sent for.

28:46.942 --> 28:50.859
Goliath knew it needed an alien
to guide and protect it.

28:50.903 --> 28:52.905
An alien with emotions,

28:52.948 --> 28:54.776
like you.

28:54.820 --> 28:56.560
Who was he?

28:56.604 --> 28:58.345
<i>He was a man</i> <i>
who stepped out of the jungle</i>

28:58.388 --> 29:00.086
<i>that I fell in love with.</i>

29:00.129 --> 29:03.306
<i>Goliath told me you would come</i> <i>
when the time is right.</i>

29:03.350 --> 29:05.221
I know now why he said
it was very important

29:05.265 --> 29:07.397
for you to have the egg.

29:07.441 --> 29:09.748
Goliath warned me there would
be people coming for it.

29:11.227 --> 29:13.882
Promise you will take care
of my baby.

29:15.318 --> 29:17.886
I promise.

29:17.930 --> 29:20.497
Harry, she's gone.

29:20.541 --> 29:22.891
They want the egg.
They won't stop.

29:22.935 --> 29:25.154
Go out the back.

29:25.198 --> 29:26.286
Okay.

29:26.329 --> 29:29.289
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

29:29.332 --> 29:35.686
<i>♪</i>

29:37.210 --> 29:38.298
Ooh!

29:38.341 --> 29:42.171
<i>♪</i>

29:42.215 --> 29:43.782
Hey!

29:43.825 --> 29:46.393
[suppressed gunshots]
- [grunts]

29:46.436 --> 29:47.829
Who the hell are these guys?

29:47.873 --> 29:54.836
<i>♪</i>

30:01.016 --> 30:03.018
[sighs]
Max is just getting

30:03.062 --> 30:04.106
to the point where I can
leave him home alone

30:04.150 --> 30:05.716
without it being
a child services issue.

30:05.760 --> 30:06.935
Hmm.

30:06.979 --> 30:08.894
Unless he gets
into the matches.

30:08.937 --> 30:10.634
I mean,
if I can handle the drunks

30:10.678 --> 30:12.462
that come through this place,

30:12.506 --> 30:13.812
kid can't be that much worse.

30:13.855 --> 30:15.901
You saying you actually
wanna have a kid?

30:15.944 --> 30:17.119
First I'd have to find
the right guy

30:17.163 --> 30:18.729
to have his life ruined by me.

30:18.773 --> 30:22.037
- [chuckles]
- Ooh, anyone special in mind?

30:22.081 --> 30:24.213
Do I have a victim in mind?

30:25.562 --> 30:27.826
Dating me is kind of like
walking into a war zone.

30:27.869 --> 30:30.785
Hey, I think you're a catch.

30:30.829 --> 30:32.004
And if you wanted to,

30:32.047 --> 30:33.396
I think you would be
a great mom.

30:33.440 --> 30:34.745
Come on.

30:34.789 --> 30:36.791
Imagine if you were pregnant.

30:36.835 --> 30:39.054
We could be pregnancy buddies.

30:39.098 --> 30:40.795
We can get them matching

30:40.839 --> 30:43.145
"This is what a feminist
looks like" onesies.

30:43.189 --> 30:45.495
I mean, you'd have to be
willing to give up the freedom

30:45.539 --> 30:48.324
to do whatever you want
whenever you want.

30:49.717 --> 30:52.633
I mean, you could just jet off
to Paris right now.

30:52.676 --> 30:54.896
But I won't.

30:54.940 --> 30:57.594
I'll just jet home
to my nail polish collection.

30:57.638 --> 31:00.162
I have a lot of nail polish.

31:00.206 --> 31:02.208
At least your baby won't make
you high when you sniff it.

31:02.251 --> 31:03.252
Take it easy.

31:03.296 --> 31:04.645
You know, it's--

31:04.688 --> 31:08.040
it's not like I know for sure
that I'm pregnant.

31:08.083 --> 31:11.130
Well, let's find out.

31:14.307 --> 31:17.223
Here at The 59, we cater to
every stage of a relationship.

31:17.266 --> 31:19.486
Condoms, pregnancy tests,
paternity tests,

31:19.529 --> 31:21.618
plus a divorce lawyer
who starts his weekend bender

31:21.662 --> 31:23.142
on Thursday afternoon.

31:23.185 --> 31:25.274
[metallic bang]
Mm.

31:25.318 --> 31:26.797
Thank God
these are still in stock.

31:26.841 --> 31:29.844
Judy goes through them
like Tic Tacs that you piss on.

31:29.888 --> 31:31.367
I don't know.

31:31.411 --> 31:33.761
I'm not sure I'm ready
for the answer yet.

31:35.458 --> 31:37.547
Not feelin' as brave as you.

31:37.591 --> 31:38.809
You didn't see me run away

31:38.853 --> 31:40.420
from the leg press
at the gym today.

31:40.463 --> 31:43.379
So you skipped one machine.
It was your first day back.

31:43.423 --> 31:45.077
When you're ready,
it'll be there.

31:46.600 --> 31:48.384
Keep it on you.

31:48.428 --> 31:50.517
When you're ready,
it'll be there.

31:50.560 --> 31:53.476
<i>[mellow rock music]</i>

31:53.520 --> 32:00.440
<i>♪</i>

32:02.529 --> 32:07.403
Why do we have to ride
on this train for two days?

32:07.447 --> 32:10.929
What if someone ties a lady
to the tracks?

32:10.972 --> 32:12.931
If they tie her lengthwise,

32:12.974 --> 32:14.584
it could derail us.

32:14.628 --> 32:16.064
It could.

32:16.108 --> 32:18.806
But it won't, because this
isn't a silent movie, Harry.

32:18.849 --> 32:20.808
And we didn't have a choice.

32:20.851 --> 32:23.854
Pretty sure TSA
won't let you on a plane

32:23.898 --> 32:25.291
with something like that
in a bag.

32:27.032 --> 32:30.252
Do you even know
if and when it will hatch?

32:30.296 --> 32:31.645
No.

32:31.688 --> 32:34.474
On my planet,
we mate with a genetic partner.

32:35.562 --> 32:37.607
The partner
who carries the offspring

32:37.651 --> 32:39.000
incubates hundreds of eggs.

32:39.044 --> 32:41.742
This is just one egg.

32:41.785 --> 32:43.962
One of my kind...

32:44.005 --> 32:46.834
mating with a human partner.

32:46.877 --> 32:50.142
I do not know
what this will look like.

32:50.185 --> 32:52.622
I do not know
when it will come.

32:52.666 --> 32:55.538
It could be hatching in a year.

32:56.670 --> 32:59.760
It could be hatching right now.

32:59.803 --> 33:01.805
Or...now.

33:01.849 --> 33:03.546
Or now.

33:03.590 --> 33:04.852
Fantastic.

33:06.332 --> 33:07.986
What are we
supposed to do now?

33:08.029 --> 33:10.684
Goliath wanted me
to have this egg.

33:10.727 --> 33:14.122
He knew what would happen
if he became impregnated.

33:14.166 --> 33:18.518
Goliath died
so I could have this baby.

33:19.780 --> 33:22.435
I'm gonna go get a tea.

33:22.478 --> 33:23.479
Do you want anything?

33:23.523 --> 33:24.524
No.

33:24.567 --> 33:27.005
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

33:27.048 --> 33:28.702
Ice cream sandwich!

33:28.745 --> 33:30.312
<i>♪</i>

33:30.356 --> 33:32.140
<i>I went to New York</i> <i>
to find an alien</i>

33:32.184 --> 33:34.664
<i>even a little like me.</i>

33:34.708 --> 33:36.492
<i>Now when I look at this egg,</i>

33:36.536 --> 33:39.321
<i>I think I have found</i> <i>
something different,</i>

33:39.365 --> 33:42.629
<i>a baby contaminated</i> <i>
with human emotion,</i>

33:42.672 --> 33:45.849
<i>part alien and part human.</i>

33:45.893 --> 33:48.374
<i>It is not a little like me.</i>

33:49.679 --> 33:51.551
<i>It is just like me.</i>

33:53.031 --> 33:55.946
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

33:55.990 --> 34:03.084
<i>♪</i>

34:09.743 --> 34:11.223
What's going on, Mike?

34:11.266 --> 34:14.052
You haven't turned the page
since you came in.

34:16.228 --> 34:17.794
I--
[clears throat]

34:17.838 --> 34:19.013
I got a bunch of these books

34:19.057 --> 34:22.538
from Abigail Hodges, and...

34:22.582 --> 34:24.714
thought they'd help me
take my mind off some stuff,

34:24.758 --> 34:26.412
but it's not working so well.

34:28.240 --> 34:29.937
Something you wanna
talk about?

34:31.591 --> 34:36.248
Share with a fellow soldier
what's on your mind?

34:38.293 --> 34:40.774
Oh,
I kind of feel stuck lately.

34:40.817 --> 34:42.645
You know, like
I'm in the middle of something,

34:42.689 --> 34:45.735
but I'm not sure which way
is the right way to go.

34:45.779 --> 34:46.954
Hmm.

34:46.997 --> 34:48.564
Look, between you and me...

34:50.262 --> 34:51.828
I think I made a mistake.

34:52.829 --> 34:55.571
I think I might've put
the wrong person behind bars.

34:57.095 --> 34:59.793
Last time I made a big mistake
like that was back in D.C.,

34:59.836 --> 35:02.752
and my partner,
he didn't go home that day.

35:02.796 --> 35:04.363
Tough break.

35:04.406 --> 35:06.234
Yeah.

35:06.278 --> 35:08.628
If I had my sage,
I'd smudge you.

35:08.671 --> 35:10.195
Mm.

35:10.238 --> 35:12.501
Free pie is a close second.

35:12.545 --> 35:15.374
- Psh, I'll take it.
- [chuckles]

35:22.076 --> 35:24.209
I was doing guard duty
in Vietnam.

35:25.775 --> 35:28.517
Dreamin' about the burgers
we'd order back home.

35:29.910 --> 35:32.304
Tellin' dirty jokes.
- [laughs]

35:33.131 --> 35:35.176
Pretendin'
we weren't scared shitless.

35:35.220 --> 35:37.570
<i>[somber music]</i>

35:37.613 --> 35:39.311
It was an ambush.

35:39.354 --> 35:42.183
My buddy hit the floor.

35:42.227 --> 35:44.533
I just stood there
like an idiot

35:44.577 --> 35:46.187
till he bled out.

35:46.970 --> 35:48.450
Jesus, Dan.

35:48.494 --> 35:50.583
Medic told me
it wasn't my fault.

35:50.626 --> 35:56.154
Called it a...
sucking chest wound.

35:56.197 --> 35:58.068
But I couldn't shake the guilt.

35:58.112 --> 36:01.071
And I ran from that mistake
for years.

36:01.115 --> 36:04.118
Almost died from it.

36:04.162 --> 36:06.816
I'm sorry.

36:06.860 --> 36:09.471
I mean, how do you even survive
something like that?

36:09.515 --> 36:12.387
It's not
about the surviving.

36:12.431 --> 36:16.522
Any soldier who's still with us
is surviving.

36:18.219 --> 36:21.004
A soldier has to prevail.

36:21.048 --> 36:23.529
Learned to honor Joe.

36:24.269 --> 36:26.096
[chuckles]
Now he's with me every day.

36:26.140 --> 36:30.492
<i>♪</i>

36:30.536 --> 36:33.016
If you wanna honor
your partner,

36:33.060 --> 36:35.280
be the best cop you can be.

36:35.323 --> 36:37.630
Put the right person
behind bars.

36:37.673 --> 36:44.593
<i>♪</i>

36:59.304 --> 37:01.523
Deputy. Hey.

37:01.567 --> 37:03.221
I've been waiting out front
for the last ten minutes.

37:03.264 --> 37:04.744
You forget
I was picking you up?

37:04.787 --> 37:05.788
Yeah, I'm sorry.

37:05.832 --> 37:07.703
I've been tied up.

37:07.747 --> 37:10.315
Just, like, police stuff.

37:11.751 --> 37:13.709
Pullin' UFOs over
for speeding again?

37:13.753 --> 37:14.884
I'm sorry.

37:14.928 --> 37:17.235
I'm just feeling
a little stupid.

37:17.931 --> 37:22.240
I posted that UFO video,
and people think it's fake.

37:22.283 --> 37:23.632
Hey, the only thing stupid
is believing

37:23.676 --> 37:25.068
what someone
on the internet thinks.

37:25.112 --> 37:26.244
Ignore them.

37:26.287 --> 37:28.376
It's not just one person.

37:28.420 --> 37:31.292
It's most of them,
and someone used a filter

37:31.336 --> 37:34.077
to change the UFO
into a doughnut.

37:34.121 --> 37:36.558
They don't even know I'm a cop.

37:36.602 --> 37:38.168
That looks pretty realistic.

37:39.082 --> 37:40.562
Now I'm hungry.

37:40.606 --> 37:42.434
Let's stop and get one
on the way home.

37:42.477 --> 37:44.000
[cell phone dings and buzzes]

37:44.044 --> 37:45.567
Sorry.

37:48.004 --> 37:50.442
I need ten more minutes.

37:50.485 --> 37:52.226
- Okay.
- Okay.

37:56.796 --> 37:59.233
I changed my mind.
I want tea--

37:59.277 --> 38:00.843
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

38:00.887 --> 38:03.542
You should've cleaned up
after yourself.

38:03.585 --> 38:05.587
Now, you're gonna give me
that egg,

38:05.631 --> 38:07.981
and you're gonna tell me
where it came from.

38:08.024 --> 38:11.593
<i>♪</i>

38:11.637 --> 38:14.335
[grunting]

38:14.379 --> 38:21.473
<i>♪</i>

38:34.703 --> 38:36.662
Ow.

38:36.705 --> 38:38.228
[grunts]

38:38.272 --> 38:44.496
<i>♪</i>

38:44.539 --> 38:45.758
You.

38:49.414 --> 38:56.508
<i>♪</i>

39:01.730 --> 39:04.037
What the--
how did that window break?

39:04.080 --> 39:05.386
I do not know.

39:05.430 --> 39:08.258
It is a very cheap train.
Everything breaks.

39:08.302 --> 39:11.131
Oh, my God.

39:11.174 --> 39:14.395
What--
what happened to your face?

39:14.439 --> 39:18.530
<i>♪</i>

39:18.573 --> 39:21.794
I may have killed
the bad woman.

39:21.837 --> 39:24.231
It's okay.
I threw her out the window.

39:25.014 --> 39:26.407
She's gone.

39:27.800 --> 39:30.890
Did you get
my ice cream sandwich?

39:30.933 --> 39:33.327
<i>♪</i>

39:36.765 --> 39:39.464
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

39:39.507 --> 39:42.075
<i>♪</i>

39:42.118 --> 39:44.947
Sir, we've been through
this room a thousand times.

39:44.991 --> 39:46.993
Do you really think
we've been missing something?

39:47.036 --> 39:48.516
Yeah, well, before,
we were trying to get

39:48.560 --> 39:50.388
in the killer's head.

39:50.431 --> 39:52.738
Maybe it's time
we try to get into Sam's.

39:52.781 --> 39:58.874
<i>♪</i>

39:58.918 --> 40:02.095
Okay, so I'm a small-town
doctor, right?

40:02.138 --> 40:03.705
Nice guy.
Whole town loves me.

40:03.749 --> 40:05.664
So why would somebody
want me dead?

40:05.707 --> 40:07.753
Medical malpractice?
I don't think so.

40:07.796 --> 40:08.971
I'm too damn good at what I do.

40:09.015 --> 40:10.451
Did I witness something?

40:10.495 --> 40:13.454
Did I know something that
made somebody wanna kill me?

40:13.498 --> 40:15.195
I was smart.

40:15.238 --> 40:19.025
If I knew something
important and dangerous,

40:19.068 --> 40:20.809
I might've written it down.

40:20.853 --> 40:22.289
Yeah, but where?

40:24.247 --> 40:26.075
[sighs]

40:28.426 --> 40:30.515
Wait.

40:30.558 --> 40:32.386
Sam loved these books.

40:32.430 --> 40:35.389
<i>[Mississippi Twilight's</i> <i>
"Here and Gone"]</i>

40:35.433 --> 40:36.869
Sir?

40:36.912 --> 40:38.827
The sex-crazed detective
in these books,

40:38.871 --> 40:40.307
when he thought
somebody was after him,

40:40.350 --> 40:41.743
he would take his case notes,
and he would put them

40:41.787 --> 40:44.050
in the back of paintings
in his office.

40:44.093 --> 40:45.878
<i>♪ In the middle</i> <i>
of the streets of Eden ♪</i>

40:45.921 --> 40:48.054
Come on.

40:48.097 --> 40:51.710
<i>♪ The four winds blow</i>

40:51.753 --> 40:53.886
Shit.

40:53.929 --> 40:56.497
<i>♪ Of my father's soul</i>

40:56.541 --> 41:00.414
<i>♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh,</i> <i>
here and gone ♪</i>

41:00.458 --> 41:01.937
[sighs]

41:03.330 --> 41:05.201
You know what?
Maybe it's just a dumb book.

41:07.073 --> 41:09.162
Even if he hid
something here,

41:09.205 --> 41:11.120
it would probably be gone
by now.

41:11.164 --> 41:13.122
I mean, we've had
three doctors since.

41:13.166 --> 41:14.994
Any one of them could've
changed these paintings.

41:15.037 --> 41:18.345
<i>♪</i>

41:18.388 --> 41:19.477
Not that one.

41:21.304 --> 41:23.002
Not this one.

41:23.045 --> 41:24.917
<i>♪ Here and gone</i>

41:24.960 --> 41:27.049
<i>♪</i>

41:27.093 --> 41:32.098
<i>♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh</i>

41:32.141 --> 41:34.579
<i>♪ Ooh, ooh</i>

41:34.622 --> 41:36.232
<i>♪</i>

41:36.276 --> 41:38.191
<i>♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh</i>

41:38.234 --> 41:40.628
- Sheriff.
- [laughs]

41:40.672 --> 41:43.718
Holy shit.

41:43.762 --> 41:45.851
<i>♪</i>

41:45.894 --> 41:47.026
[chuckles]

41:49.376 --> 41:51.857
[engine shuts off]

41:51.900 --> 41:55.295
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

41:55.338 --> 41:59.168
<i>Patience must be nearer</i> <i>
to my planet than New York.</i>

41:59.212 --> 42:03.521
<i>When I am here,</i> <i>
I feel closer to home.</i>

42:05.000 --> 42:06.262
You gonna tell me
what's goin' on?

42:06.306 --> 42:09.265
You haven't talked
this whole ride.

42:11.093 --> 42:12.573
I don't like it
when you're quiet.

42:12.617 --> 42:13.835
Makes me nervous.

42:15.837 --> 42:18.753
[sighs]
The alien we went to see

42:18.797 --> 42:20.233
was dead.

42:20.276 --> 42:22.278
But it gave birth to an egg,

42:22.322 --> 42:24.280
and now it's in Harry's bag.

42:25.891 --> 42:28.110
I liked it more
when you were quiet.

42:28.981 --> 42:35.901
<i>♪</i>

42:35.944 --> 42:36.989
Me too.

42:37.032 --> 42:38.860
Congratulations!

42:38.904 --> 42:41.036
I heard you adopted a baby.

42:41.080 --> 42:43.952
Do not worry.
It has not hatched yet.

42:43.996 --> 42:47.303
If it did, you would know.

42:47.347 --> 42:49.828
It would probably spit acid.

42:49.871 --> 42:51.438
[car door slams]
- [sighs]

42:51.481 --> 42:55.050
It'll be a relief that
we put that egg somewhere safe.

42:55.094 --> 42:57.705
Finally a use for that
stupid bunker of yours.

42:57.749 --> 43:00.186
I built that stupid bunker
to save your life.

43:00.229 --> 43:02.144
- Uh-huh.
- So that everyone in the world

43:02.188 --> 43:04.320
would die but me and you.

43:04.364 --> 43:06.018
Thanks for including me.

43:06.061 --> 43:07.280
all: Surprise!

43:07.323 --> 43:08.586
Ah!

43:08.629 --> 43:11.850
[laughs] Happy birthday,
Dr. Vanderspeigle.

43:11.893 --> 43:13.416
Glad to have you
back in Patience.

43:13.460 --> 43:14.417
Speech!

43:15.593 --> 43:17.464
Get out of my house!

43:17.507 --> 43:20.075
[laughter]

43:20.119 --> 43:22.077
[egg cracks]
